# class: architecture
# schema: kind | name | role | source
# source: docs/architecture.md
# recipe: builtin:architecture

section | Overview | top-level orientation + scope | @docs/architecture.md#overview
section | API contract | enumerates endpoints + auth | @docs/architecture.md#api
component | gateway | edge auth, request routing, rate limiting | @docs/architecture.md#gateway
component | service-tier | business logic, owns DB transactions | @docs/architecture.md#services
component | store | PostgreSQL primary + read replicas | @docs/architecture.md#store

# Recipe: top-level structure of the architecture doc.
#   kind=section → top-level heading + one-line purpose.
#   kind=component → service/tier/store/client named in the source + one-line responsibility.
# FR/NFR tables, API matrix, UI states, glossary live in their own index files (architecture-fr.idx, api-matrix.yaml, ui-states.yaml, constraints.yaml, glossary.idx).
# Lossless rule: every top-level section + every named component has a row here.
